// SECTION 5 GMM
********************************************************************************


// Exercise 1 {Public spending in the US}


**********************************************
webuse "expend.dta", clear

// 1. Regress by OLS
regress expend aid inc pop
est store ols
// One step GMM
gmm (expend-{b0}-{b1}*aid-{b2}*inc-{b3}*pop), onestep instruments(aid pop inc)
est store gmm1
// Two step GMM
gmm (expend-{b0}-{b1}*aid-{b2}*inc-{b3}*pop), twostep instruments (aid pop inc)
est store gmm2
// Compare results
est table ols gmm1 gmm2, se
* Note that all the coefficients are the same, but s.e. are different

// 2. Regress with different instruments
gmm (expend-{b0}-{b1}*aid-{b2}*inc-{b3}*pop), instruments (ps pop inc)
est store gmminst
// None of these coefficients are significant!

est table gmm1 gmm2 gmminst, se


**********************************************

// Exercise 3 {Estimating the Klein model by GMM}


**********************************************
webuse "klein.dta", clear

// 1. Estimate consumption equation
	// By OLS
g w	=	w1+w2
reg cn p w L1.p
est store ols1

	// By GMM
gmm (cn-{a1}*p-{a2}*w-{a3}*L1.p-{a0}), instruments (p w L1.p)
est store gmm1

est table ols1 gmm1, se title ("Comparison of OLS and GMM estimates for consumption equation")
* Note that the estimated coefficients are the same, but standard errors are different.


// 2. Estimate investment equation
	// By OLS
reg i p L1.p klag
est store ols2

	// By GMM
gmm (i-{b1}*p-{b2}*L1.p-{b3}*klag-{b0}), instruments (p L1.p klag)
est store gmm2

est table ols2 gmm2, se title("Comparison of OLS and GMM estimates for investment equation")
* Note that the estimated coefficients are the same, but standard errors are different.
